reviews.subject: Biology
reviews.review: Dr. Johnson's lectures are engaging and informative. She's always willing to help during office hours.

reviews.subject: Computer Science
reviews.review: Excellent teacher! Prof. Chang explains complex concepts in a way that's easy to understand.

reviews.subject: Psychology
reviews.review: Dr. Rodriguez knows her subject well, but her assignments can be unclear at times.

reviews.subject: Mathematics
reviews.review: Prof. Lee's passion for math is contagious. His problem-solving techniques are very helpful.

reviews.subject: Chemistry
reviews.review: Dr. Patel's lab sessions are well-organized and her explanations are crystal clear.

reviews.subject: History
reviews.review: Prof. Brown's lectures can be dry and monotonous. More interactive sessions would help.

reviews.subject: English Literature
reviews.review: Dr. White's analysis of classic texts is insightful. She encourages critical thinking.

reviews.subject: Physics
reviews.review: Prof. Green is knowledgeable, but his pace can be too fast for some students to follow.

reviews.subject: Sociology
reviews.review: Dr. Garcia's class discussions are thought-provoking and relevant to current issues.

reviews.subject: Economics
reviews.review: Prof. Wilson uses real-world examples to illustrate economic principles effectively.

reviews.subject: Art History
reviews.review: Dr. Thompson's passion for art is inspiring. Her virtual museum tours are a highlight.

reviews.subject: Political Science
reviews.review: Prof. Ivanov's lectures are informative, but he could improve on encouraging class participation.

reviews.subject: Neuroscience
reviews.review: Dr. Chen's research-oriented approach gives great insight into current developments in the field.

reviews.subject: Philosophy
reviews.review: Prof. Adams' Socratic method of teaching really helps in developing critical thinking skills.

reviews.subject: Genetics
reviews.review: Dr. Goldstein makes complex genetic concepts understandable. Her office hours are very helpful.

reviews.subject: Environmental Science
reviews.review: Prof. Martinez's field trips are great, but his lectures could use more structure.

reviews.subject: Linguistics
reviews.review: Dr. Lee's interactive language exercises make learning linguistics both fun and effective.

reviews.subject: Business Administration
reviews.review: Prof. Taylor's real-world business experience adds valuable context to theoretical concepts.

reviews.subject: Anthropology
reviews.review: Dr. Patel's diverse case studies provide a comprehensive view of human cultures.

reviews.subject: Statistics
reviews.review: Prof. Anderson's explanations can be confusing. More practice problems would be helpful.
